{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bc5d1348-69c4-4319-ad4a-e6de0dda6b76","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the VSTest options are replaced by platform-native flags. Pass them after `--` when using `dotnet test` on .NET 8:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test \\\n  -- \\\n  --treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Integration]\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n\n| VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|\n| `--filter \"Category=Integration\"` | `--treenode-filter \"/**/*[Category=Integration]\"` |\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` — enables `--report-trx`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` — enables `--coverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` — enables `--crashdump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` — enables `--hangdump`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e89501c4-ad3c-4d4d-97ea-8c7f62f3f61a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure changes. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter` (same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you use a runsettings file\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` maps to `--crashdump` and `--blame-hang` with its timeout option become `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout` respectively\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8+, the command syntax shifts, though some options like `--filter` remain compatible. I'm working through the exact parameter mappings to give you the precise migration path. after the `--` separator. For .NET 8 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I can either pass platform-specific options through `dotnet test --` or run the test executable directly with those same options. Let me verify the exact syntax here since there are some nuances around how .NET 8 handles this versus .NET 9+.\n\nThe key flags I need to account for are the filter syntax (which differs between the old `--filter` and the newer `--treenode-filter`), the TRX report generation (requires the TrxReport extension), code coverage with the CodeCoverage collector, and the blame-related options that have been renamed in the newer platform (`--crashdump`, `--hangdump`, and `--hangdump-timeout`). I should clarify which approach actually works in .NET 8 and what dependencies are required.","outputTokens":1438,"requestId":"67E0:CA1D0:2A55B8E:2EA3F60:69FD34F5"},"id":"b2656edb-bc3b-4276-824a-4565d6fbf438","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:57:50.526Z","parentId":"f7a65d95-84be-4fdb-a6e1-3337d8431d7d"}
